The article is a transcript of remarks made by President Joe Biden and First Lady Jill Biden during a Nowruz reception at the White House. Nowruz is the Persian New Year celebration, and the reception was the first of its kind held on such a scale at the White House. The President and First Lady acknowledged the challenges faced by many families around the world and expressed hope for renewal and transformation. They also recognized the courage of Iranian women fighting for their rights and the importance of holding Iranian officials accountable. The President highlighted the importance of immigration and diversity in shaping the United States and expressed optimism for the future of the country. The article concludes with a musical performance by Sahba Motallebi and Rana Mansour.